...The darkness was complete. No light shined from within. He could hear rustling from somewhere down below. The stairs seemed to go on forever. Something drew close. He could hear the humans behind him trying to scream. He stopped his descent, and turned.<br>
...His eyes, dark as the tomb around him, cut through the blackness. They saw a black robed being floating down the stairs behind him. He did not move or attempt to stop it. He merely waited. The creature passed through the humans and they shook violently. It floated up to him. Red eyes burned from under its hood. Its voice filled the tomb.<br>
...&quot;Interloper, what lies here lies not for you... What lies here was buried in ages past for the good of the empire...For the justice of the empire...You have violated this tomb and you have forfeited your life...&quot;<br>
...The pale man looked into the burning red eyes. No emotion crossed his face. His white hair blew across his eyes. &quot;I have no life to forfeit, Guardian. Go your way.&quot;<br>
...The Guardian hissed and a cold, bone chilling wind blew over them. The humans shook from fear. Even the shadows trembled. The pale man did not move.<br>
...&quot;Look into my eyes, Guardian. See what has come here into your abode. Your presence is irrelevent. Deter me, and your existence ends.&quot;<br>
...The Guardian rose up before him and suddenly a great scythe arched through the air at the pale man. The scythe never found its mark.<br>
...The pale man struck out with an open hand. Black magic howled through the air around him. The scythe was sent spiraling down into the tomb below. The Guardian was torn in every direction by unseen hands. It wailed and cried as it fell apart. Finally, its magic ceased to be. A simple black shroud fell to the steps before the pale man, empty. The pale man turned and continued to walk down.<br>
...The stairs led deep into the heart of the undermountains. No light guided them. The pale man did not need it. The shadows followed with their prisoners bound in ebon tenticles.<br>
...They reached the bottom of the stairs. The pale man stepped down onto the cold stone floor of the tomb of Notuanot. He glanced down and where his feet touched the ground, it caught fire. He left a burning trail in his wake. the shadows moved aside and carried the human couple away from harm. <br>
...The tomb was now alight. In its center was a vast pit. Bones littered the pit. The remains of loyal Crusaders who had likely sacrificed themselves to some great magic that was used to bind Notuanot's soul in the abyss forever. The Keeper of the Abyss had found his soul. The Keeper was here now, to bring it back into the world.<br>
...The pit sank down at a slope and at its center it was charred back. They had burned his remains with their magic to seal him here. A single skeleton lay in the center. Its frame was undeniably Iksar. <br>
...The pale man stepped down into the pit. As he did, the bones of the sacrificed Crusaders jumped to life. All around him, they rose up. The pale man smiled. His eyes surveyed the host that rose up against him now, a small army of undead Crusaders. <br>
...&quot;Woe to you sheep!&quot; the pale man's voice boomed throughout the tomb. &quot;Have you not guessed who I am yet? You constantly stand in my way, first the living, then the dead. You are dust in the wind. I AM the wind. I am Sauroh! I am Death! And I have come for what belongs to me!&quot; Sauroh threw his cloak aside. His blood red armor gleamed in the tomblight. He unsheathed a sword of bone and began to cut a path through the skeletal Crusaders. They threw themselves at him and were dissected. <br>
... His sword not only cut at their bones but also shattered the magic of the spell that had made them. The spell that also bound Notuanot's soul.<br>
...Waves of flame shot out from him. Crusaders toppled to the ground from the blows of Sauroh's bonesword. The flames ate their bones until one last Crusader stood. It lurched forward and made its attack.<br>
...Sauroh turned to walk away. As he did, he gestured idly at the last Crusader. Its bones flew apart and its reanimated existence came to an end. Sauroh walked to the center of the pit.<br>
...Sauroh looked down at the corpse. They had buried him as they had slain him, naked. His flesh and scales had long since rotted away.<br>
...The shadows dragged the humans into the pit. Sauroh turned toward them. The shadows let go of the male and he fell forward. He struggled to his feet. Sauroh grasped him by the throat.<br>
...Sauroh looked into his wide, frightened eyes and said, &quot;Do you know who I am child? Because I know who you are. You are Enoch of Qeynos. You were out in the streets when I took you. What were you doing out that late?&quot;<br>
...Enoch gasped but could not speak. His words wanted to come out. He wanted to confess his sins in hopes this dark God would forgive him, in hopes that someone would forgive him and free him of this fate. But he could not. something was inside him and it had sealed off his voice. It was mortal fear.<br>
...Sauroh shrugged. &quot;It doesn't matter. I don't need your words. I don't need your fear. I just need your life force.&quot;<br>
...Sauroh held onto Enoch and rose into the air. He hovered over the corpse in the center of the pit. He held Enoch over the pit.<br>
...Enoch trembled and held onto Sauroh's arm with both of his own. He struggled to look below him, as he was sure something horrible was happening. It was.<br>
...An invisible force, a hungry force, rose up from the pile of bones. It pulled at Enoch's flesh. Enoch's flesh began to tear and come off. He suddenly found his voice and screamed.<br>
...The force ripped and tore away at Enoch. His flesh came off in great bloody gobs and fell down into the pit and onto the pile of bones below. The flesh began to crawl over the bones and fill them. <br>
...More of Enoch's flesh was torn away by the invisible force and as it fell it began to take on the shape of organs. It began to fill the skeleton's rib cage with a heart and intestines. The invisible force tore away at Enoch's exposed muscles now. Enoch went into seizures and frothed at the mouth. He shook horribly as his muscles and flesh were torn away and fell to the pit below.<br>
...The skeletal form below, now with a complete set of lungs, a heart, and a stomach, began to tremble. One boney hand raised up. A gob of flesh fell right onto it and crawled over it. The flesh of Enoch became Notuanot's muscle tissue and cartilage.<br>
...Enoch's legs were now eaten away up to his hips. His blood poured down and joined with the rest. It crawled across Notuanot's skeletal form and became kidneys, spleen. It continued to cover his skeleton in muscle tissue.<br>
...The invisible force tore at Enoch's torso now. His own organs were torn away. He convulsed one last time, his eyes rolling all the way back into his head, as his heart was pulled out and fell to the pit, crawling onto the skeletal form, becoming Notuanot's eyes and the musculature of his face.<br>
...The last of Enoch fell away and was absorbed by the trembling body below. Sauroh cast his skeleton aside. As he did, the marrow oozed from Enoch's bones and dribbled down into the pit. The half-formed creature below lurched and crawled to the edge of the pit. Its eyes had no lids, its face had no scales to cover it. It put its face down into the pool of bone marrow and began to drink of it.<br>
...The female had witnessed all of this. She trembled as Sauroh reached for her throat. She screamed. Sauroh lifted her into the air and hovered out over the pit.<br>
...She kicked and screamed. Sauroh reared back once and slapped her. She moaned and wailed. The creature below rolled back over and looked up. It saw Sauroh above it, with the scared human girl.<br>
...The girl trembled and mouthed the word &quot;no&quot; over and over. The invisible force began to claw at her body. It tore out her hair and scalp and it fell down into the pit...<br>
....................................................................................<br>
<br>
...Sauroh waited for the marrow to drip down from the skeleton he held now. A piece of cartiladge that held its leg on snapped and its skeletal leg fell into the pit. Notuanot crawled across the pit. He greedily snatched up the legbone. He bit into it and sucked the marrow from it.<br>
...Sauroh tossed the skeleton aside. Before him now, in the pit, he beheld his newly created demon. &quot;Tell me your name,&quot; Sauroh commanded, in lizardman. <br>
...The creature struggled to its feet. It stood before him, naked, whole. &quot;I am... Notuanot.&quot;<br>
...Sauroh nodded. &quot;Come here, Notuanot.&quot; The Lizardman lurched forward on its new legs, formed from the flesh and blood of innocence. It stepped out of the pit that had been its tomb.<br>
...Notuanot ran his scaled hands over his body, as if making sure everything was there. His fingers slipped into a gaping crater in his chest and he pulled his hand away, startled.<br>
...Sauroh smirked. There was indeed a huge hole in the center of Notuanot's chest, where his heart should be. Sauroh lifted a bag in his hand, that hung on a chord around his neck. He reached into it, and pulled something out. It was a heart. Still beating. Blood dripped from it onto the ground at his feet.<br>
...Notuanot took a few cautious steps forward and held out his hands expectantly. &quot;Looking for this?&quot; Sauroh asked him. Notuanot nodded.<br>
...Sauroh shook his head and put the heart back in the bag. &quot;I don't think so. That is the talisman by which I bind you. As long as I hold it, I hold you.&quot;<br>
...Notuanot put his open hands down at his sides and kneeled before Sauroh. &quot;You are the one. You are The Lord of Tears.&quot;<br>
...Sauroh smiled. &quot;Yes. I am the God of Death. Come to me. Let me fill your cup. Let me begin the ending. The ending of all.&quot;<br>
...Notuanot leaned forward on one knee. He spread one hand out open on the ground before him. He had no sword. He rested the other hand on his bare knee in the traditional Iksar bow. &quot;I have come, my master. I am here to do your bidding, my master.&quot;<br>
...&quot;Yes,&quot; said Sauroh. &quot;You are. You are my hand. You are the hand of Death.<br>
...&quot;You will clutch at the throats of my enemies,&quot; said Sauroh. &quot;You will lay them, lifeless, on the ground at my feet.<br>
You will pile them up like kindling. I will start the fire. The fire will burn. And it will burn Norrath to ash!&quot;<br>
...Sauroh raised his hands into the air. Magic began to gather around him. &quot;One more thing. One final step.&quot; Darkness came. It rapped itself around Notuanot and lifted him into the air. He did not struggle. He had been remade. He was his master's tool now, to be shaped and molded as The Lord of Tears saw fit. <br>
...The darkness seeped into his flesh and into his bones. It filled his eyes and they began to glow red. When the darkness was all inside Notuanot, he collapsed to the ground.<br>
...&quot;There,&quot; Sauroh said as Notuanot struggled to his knees. &quot;That shall come to be known as Notuanot's Curse. Whenever you strike down another being, it shall rise again when I call it, to come march in my undead army. You will strike down humans. You will strike down other Iksar. <br>
...&quot;You will kill, without prejudice, without caring, without restraint. When I chose one to be marked for my own, you will take them. Your previous life is gone. I do not care for your previous quarrels. I only care for what you can do for me. And what you can do for me, Hand... is kill!&quot;<br>
...Notuanot held his hand out in front of him and closed it into a fist. He looked up at the Lord of Tears with burning red ember eyes. &quot;I... am. I... kill.&quot;<br>
...&quot;Yes!&quot; Sauroh clasped Notuanot's hand and pulled him to his feet. &quot;Kill for me! Kill for me! Harvest. Go! Go out into the world. Drink from its cup. End its beginning!&quot;<br>
...Notuanot bowed deeply before the Lord of Tears. He then loaped off into the night. He climbed the stairs of his tomb. <br>
....................................................................................<br>
<br>
...He went out into the Frontier Mountains. He killed. He went to the Dreadlands. He killed. He crossed an ocean and arrived at the city of men. He killed. And each time a foe fell before him, they rotted into the ground. Marked by the Curse of Notuanot. One day, the Lord of Tears would call them. And when he did, a great host of undead would rise up, the Bearers of the Curse. They would rise up and sweep across Norrath.<br>
...But until that day, Notuanot kills. And the Lord of Tears fills the abyss with the souls of his victims...<br>
